This paper deals with image fusion, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The application of the proposed method is demonstrated in biomedical infrared spectroscopic microscopy, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of regularization techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of optimization algorithms and computational methods is also mentioned, which could fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
